    "body": "I see 3 solutions:\r\n\r\nEasiest (user PoV):\r\n- One-liner or multiple docker-compose files that initialize (possibly through scripts) & run everything.\r\n\r\nEasiest(?) PoV:\r\n- K8s, I'm not very familliar with it but AFAIK you can convert docker-compose files to k8s with kompose.\r\n\r\nComplicated or for production:\r\n - Integration through puppeth (see cmd/puppeth/*)\r\n\r\nSimple but without dependencies:\r\n - Nightly build to provides signed binaries\r\n\r\nI would like to hear a little bit more about k8s, I don't know that much except from what I could see from the documentation but it seems to have an easy web interface, that would be more user friendly that a command line docker, @prestonvanloon have you played with that a little bit ?",
